/* Biology */Reference to capillarity was incorrect. Capillarity occurs at liquid-air interfaces, which do not exist in functional xylem; the water column in functioning xylem is continuous, and the interface with air instead occurs distal to the xylem, at the surfaces of living cells in leaves. This is a common misconception. Source: I have a PhD in biophysical plant physiology and plant water relations.
